  "query": "#1 - The default permissions for a registered agent (in this case an LLM connecting to Unimatrix deployed locally through STDIO) will recieve READ, SEARCH, WRITE.  The change, is that there will be no permissive auto_enroll to get it.  We are changing the fundamental authentication (which today is agent_id, passed by the LLM filling an agent_id parameter (not security), to structurally requiring the LLM to be authenticated.  At first, it will be though an env variable set OUTSIDE the LLM (assuming settings.json setting) that unimatrix will recognize this LLM as authenticated and granted Read, WRITE, Search. This is the scope of WO-2. . In the future, Unimatrix will be centralized and the LLM will connect through HTTP, and at that time, Unimatrix will require Oauth to authenticate the LLM.",
